        content: `<div class="container-fluid mt-3"> <div class="row contentfixer p-0"> <div class="col-md-12 col-12"> <h4 class="Guidetravel ">Changthang</h4> <p class="introAguide"> This area represents India's Tran Himalaya region due to its cold desert environment and harsh climatic conditions in winters. The ecosystem has suffered a lot due to harsh weather conditions and thus many wildlife animals migrate to lower regions in winters. The Changthang region is home to more than 3500 Tibetan refugees who primarily depends upon livestock for their food.<br><br>It is situated at an altitude of 14,600 meters above sea level in Rushpo Valley. The land is home to the Changpa nomads and stretches from Eastern Ladakh to approximately 1600 kilometers east into Tibet. The climate of Changthang is quite unpredictable and can result in thunderstorms at times.</p> </div> <div class="row p-0 contentfixer"> <div class="col-md-12 col-12"> <h4 class="Guidetravel ">Best Time to Travel </h4> <p class="introAguide"> The best time to visit Changthang, Ladakh, depends on your preferences and activities. Summer (June to September) is the peak season with mild temperatures (15°C to 30°C) and open roads, perfect for trekking and outdoor adventures. Autumn (September to October) offers pleasant weather and stunning landscapes as the vegetation changes color. Winter (November to April) is extremely cold, with heavy snowfall closing many roads, but it provides a unique experience of snow-covered landscapes and frozen lakes. Ensure to check current conditions, permits, and road accessibility for a smooth and enjoyable trip. </p> </div> </div> <div class="row contentfixer p-0"> <div class="col-md-12 col-12"> <h4 class="Guidetravel ">Route to Changthnag </h4> <p class="introAguide">To reach Changthang, Ladakh, start by reaching Leh, the main city in the region. You can either fly to Leh's airport or take a road trip from Srinagar or Manali. Spend a day acclimatizing in Leh due to the high altitude. From Leh, travel to Pangong Lake, a journey of about 5-6 hours, passing through picturesque landscapes and high mountain passes like Chang La. Explore Pangong Lake and the surrounding areas, experiencing the unique beauty of Changthang. To visit Tso Moriri, another stunning lake in Changthang, return to Leh and then head southeast toward Chumathang and Puga. The journey offers diverse landscapes, including hot springs and wildlife. After exploring Changthang, return to Leh, taking in the monasteries and markets. Always check current road conditions and obtain necessary permits for restricted areas before the trip. </p> </div> <h4 class=" text-center Guidetravel ">Best Places to Visit </h4> </div> </div> </div>`,
